small  percentage of the server actually comes to this board.<br>
<br>
Look at those who do. They are the people that actually put together raids.  They are the ones with initiative.  They are the guild leaders and officers of just about any respectable, raid level guild you can name.  Period.<br>
<br>
Yes, maybe 5% of the server comes here.  But its the 5% that make the action possible for the rest of the people.<br>
<br>
The ones who put together, organize, plan for wipe outs, that come here.<br>
<br>
Many people who reach raid level are referred here at once.  It is absolutely the best place to sign up for raids.<br>
<br>
So, does it matter what percentage of people actually come here? I say definately not.   Im just sick of this point being used as a justification for Free For All, or as proof reservations don't work.<br>
<br>
Ask anyone who has been on 2 plus plane raids if they know about this board and the reservation system.  I bet they do.  Ask anyone running a successful hate, fear, whateva raid, and I bet they posted here.<br>
<br>
